From: FIXME <FIXME>
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] platform: int3472: Add MSI Prestige 13 AI+ Evo A2VMG
 board data

Add TPS68470 regulator, GPIO, and I2C daisy-chain configuration for the
MSI Prestige 13 AI+ Evo A2VMG (board MS-13Q3, Lunar Lake / IPU7).

The built-in webcam uses an OV5675 sensor behind a TPS68470 PMIC.  The
PMIC's GPIO 1 and GPIO 2 serve as the I2C daisy-chain path, so
daisy-chain mode must be enabled before the sensor driver probes.
Sensor reset and powerdown are wired to GPIO 9 and GPIO 7 respectively.

Regulators:
  CORE (1.2 V)  -> OV5675 dvdd
  ANA  (2.8 V)  -> OV5675 avdd
  VSIO (1.8 V)  -> OV5675 dovdd
  VIO  (1.8 V)  -> always-on (PMIC I/O level)

Signed-off-by: FIXME <FIXME>
